{{italic title}} '''''For Gordon Bunshaft''''' is a 2006 sculpture by [[Dan Graham]], installed at the [[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]] in Washington, D.C.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirshhorn.si.edu/collection/resource-centre/#detail=/bio/smithsonians-hirshhorn-museum-and-sculpture-garden-acquires-new-sculpture-for-gordon-bunshaft-by-dan-graham/&collection=resource-centre|title=Smithsonian's Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden Acquires New Sculpture: "For Gordon Bunshaft" by Dan Graham|accessdate=May 2, 2013|publisher=[[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]]}}</ref> The work, which refers to American architect [[Gordon Bunshaft]], was installed by the reflection pool of the Sunken Sculpture Garden on May 30, 2008.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gosmithsonian.com/museums/hirshhorn-museum-and-sculpture-garden/|title=Explore: Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden|accessdate=May 2, 2013|publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]]}}</ref>
