[[File:Medemblik - Stoomgemaal Vier Noorder Koggen.jpg|thumb]] The '''Medemblik steam museum''' or Netherlands Steam Machine Museum is a [[museum]] in [[Medemblik]], West-Friesland, the [[Netherlands]]. The museum is an Anchor point on the [[European Route of Industrial Heritage]]. <ref name=ERIH> {{cite web |url=http://www.erih.net/nc/anchor-points/detail.html?user_erihobjects_pi2%5Bpointer%5D=0&user_erihobjects_pi2%5Bmode%5D=1&user_erihobjects_pi2%5BshowUid%5D=18481&user_erihobjects_pi2%5Bregionalroute%5D=0&user_erihobjects_pi2%5BanchorOnly%5D=1&user_erihobjects_pi2%5BmembersOnly%5D=0|title=ERIH: Netherlands Steam Machine Museum |date=2014 |ref=harv |publisher=European Route of Industrial Heritage |accessdate=15 January 2015 }} </ref> The pumping station is a [[rijksmonument]] (28371). ==Context== In 1984 the old pumping station, ''Vier Noorder Koggen'', was preserved in the shape of a museum, using the private collection of mr. Jongert and on site machinery. In 2012 it was upgraded. <ref name=ERIH/>
