{{italic title}} In '''''S v D''''', an important case in South African criminal law, the appellant had attempted to rape an eleven-year-old girl. He was a 44-year-old first offender. The complainant had not suffered physical injuries; there was no evidence of psychological damage. The sentence was altered on appeal to three years' imprisonment, half suspended.
== See also == * [[South African criminal law]]
== References == * ''S v D'' 1995 (2) SACR 502 (C).
